The problem is when unexpected variables are overwritten. It would be better to have a mandatory list of allowed variables that can be extracted.<p><pre><code>    $login = &#x27;1234&#x27;;
    extract(array(&#x27;login&#x27;=>true, &#x27;messsage&#x27;=>&#x27;hacker&#x27;), &#x27;message&#x27;);
    var_dump($login_, $message);
    // => $login=&#x27;1234&#x27;, $message=&#x27;hacker&#x27;
</code></pre>
(pardon my rusty PHP)
